File: Kurt-Lee Arendse during a training session. Shaun Roy/BackpagePix PRETORIA - Kurt-Lee Arendse has penned a new, long-term contract with the Vodacom Bulls.
The 26-year-old has already notched up 31 caps for the Tshwane side since joining them in 2020. An internationally acclaimed rugby player, Arendse is a Blitzbok and received his first Springbok call-up in July last, with a debut against Wales. He now has seven caps for South Africa. He has also been instrumental in multiple Sevens World Series victories and has won Super Rugby Unlocked and the Currie Cup. Bulls CEO Edgar Rathbone has referred to Arendse as a ‘fan favourite’.